ğŸ§  Behavior Flow

1. Heartbeat Invocation

The CI triggers the orchestrator hourly.

It re-verifies hashes, recomputes Merkle roots, and checks peer nodes via federate.py.



2. Lineage Renewal

The current Merkle root is merged with previous lineage in planetary_chain.json.

Old roots are never deleted; they accumulate as a tree of time.



3. Attestation Cycle

Each verification produces a new signature placeholder in attestation.json.

When Ed25519 keys are available, the Codex signs itself.



4. Interplanetary Sync

Updated manifests are pushed to IPFS automatically; returned CIDs refresh interplanetary_links.json.



5. Self-Healing Commit

Any discrepancy triggers automated reversion to last verified state and recommit under â€œSelf-Repairâ€.



6. Self-Replication

The Codex publishes its state to all configured mirrors.

Peers validate new manifests through consensus; divergent nodes auto-heal or quarantine themselves.





